      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera, featuring the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. This 996.2 generation example delivers linear power through a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transaxle. Critical preventative maintenance has been executed, including an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a rear main seal replacement. The chassis remains taut, utilizing a factory-spec MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry that provides exceptional lateral grip and communicative steering feedback. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with its mileage, the drivetrain is robust, with consistent compression across all cylinders and a recent AOS replacement. A driver-focused machine with a clean rev range and a visceral exhaust note.",
